The destructive nature of true power is born of chaos--and the dark lord Rainier rose from such disorder! Learn of Rainier¹s cruel youth as the brutality of his past bears the calling of his present, and his unrelenting pursuit of power. Meanwhile, the bonds of love between Malikai and Sonia reach a breaking point as Jayden¹s presence finally divides the two young lovers‹potentially for good. And Grace, along with a growing group of allies, is reunited with a familiar face from her past‹and particularly no stranger to the age of magic! The magic has returned and it¹s here to stay. Make sure you¹re a part of the next exciting chapter in the storied SOULFIRE mythology!
name: Friends And Enemies
Karorpati(Millionaire)

description: Azrael follows a deadly series of attacks on Order of Purity members to Europe where he confronts members of a cult who escaped Gotham City in the 2009 Bat-family Annuals. To learn secrets behind his cursed uniform, will Azrael be forced to act as the host for the resurrected Eighth Deadly Sin of Man?
name: Let Him Who Is Without Sin, Part One

description: Patsy in her own special!

An issue of the Tiny Titans presenting a new team and a new type of heroes. The issue is presenting THE SUPER-PETS.
 
Detailed

Superman-Family related pets (Beppo, Krypto, Comet, and Streaky) are flying around town getting alot of attention. So Robin dresses up a cow in a cowl, it fails to have the same dramatic effect.

In "Sound Check" cats are meowing on a fence near Titans Tree-House and Streaky goes out to join them. However Streaky's super-powered (off-tune) meows shatter nearby windows and give everyone else a headache.

Meanwhile in Metropolis, Titano the giant gorilla just escape from the circus. The mild-mannered dressed Beppo changes in a nearby telephone booth and flies off to intervene. The two chatter in ape and apparently all Titano wants are bananas, cows, a dissert bowl and two staws in order to make a giant banana milkshake.

Back in the Titans Tree-House, Supergirl attempts to engage Streaky with a ball of yarn. the cat however is unimpressed and super-smacks it away, hitting a UFO in outer space.

Later, the Super Pets ask to use the Titans Tree-House for their own secret meetings. The Green Lanterns drop off B'Dg and Brainiac 5 drops off Proty for the meeting. While Ace shows up with a new partner of his own, a robin named Robin.

In "Super Fetch", Conner is throwing a stick for Krypto while Streaky watches on, unimpressed. The game ends when Krypto returns with an entire tree instead of just the stick.

And finally Beast Boy turns himself into an ape to be apart of Titans Apes (which includes Beppo and Titano).
name: Got Cow?,Tune a Tuna,Banana Splittin',Travelin',Bark!,Giant Sized!

This one-shot comic follows a pair of female magicians who use mysticism in their bounty hunting adventures.  The copyright holders of Dirty Pair argued with this comic, saying it was infringing on their characters.
Mirage and Mrs. Incredible are on a mission together. Dash, Mr.Incredible, and Frozone investigates a break in. Violet has problems because she can never speak to Xander.
name: Secrets and Lies Part 2

description: Blythe's pilot's test has been anything but ordinary. She's discovered a lost manuscript by Jules Verne and traveled back in time to inspire the mysterious author-pilot St. Exupery. But the last leg of her journey proves the most treacherous when she encounters a recreation of one of the most dangerous aviation feats ever attempted.
name: A History of the Future, Part Three

description: BEST-SELLING AUTHOR LAURELL K. HAMILTON'S FAN-FAVORITE VAMPIRE HUNTER RETURNS! Anita Blake walked away from her last case with more than a few bruises--but those wounds are nothing compared to the scrapes that lie ahead in this blood-soaked adaptation of Hamilton's third erotic thriller. To find a killer targeting the undead, Anita must descend into the dangerous, supernatural demimonde operated by the master vampire Jean-Claude. It will take all of Anita's wits to survive THE CIRCUS OF THE DAMNED!
name: Circus of the Damned: The Charmer, 1 of 5

volume.name: Anita Blake, Vampire Hunter: Circus of the Damned - The Charmer

description: A battle in outer space tests G-Tex Wolf Brady to the limit – especially when a ruthless computer hacker makes his latest challenge even more dangerous!
name: Space Watch

description: Few authors are able to capture an honest snapshot of everyday life the way Harvey Pekar can. From ruminations on jazz musicians to back problems and traffic tickets, Pekar writes in a clear, unsentimental voice that not only explores the mundane, but celebrates it as well. This time out, Pekar focuses his sharp literary eye on Robert McNeill, an ordinary man who's lived an extraordinary life. McNeill recounts his time spent as a G.I. in Vietnam, on a tour through that surreal and horrific landscape that even now, thirty years later, we're struggling to define. Unsung Hero is a tale of cynicism and endurance, tempered by McNeill's distinct sense of humor and Pekar's touching wit.
name: Robert McNeill (Part 1)

description: Harvey Pekar continues his character study of Vietnam veteran Robert McNeill. Far more than a typical war story, Pekar and McNeill journey through the nuances of the experience, dissecting what it meant for Robert to be a black man in an already racially charged environment, and his interactions with the influences -- both friendly and unfriendly -- that surrounded him. Once again, Harvey Pekar masterfully illuminates a subtle aspect of the human condition that few others are willing or able to tackle.
name: Robert McNeill (Part 2)

description: This issue marks the conclusion to Harvey Pekar's fascinating and illuminating biography of Robert McNeill. With just a few weeks left in his tour of duty, nineteen-year-old McNeill's only thoughts are of escaping Vietnam's violently surrealistic landscape and returning home to the United States. But to do so, he must stay one step ahead of the enemies who try to take his life, the depression and nihilism that permeate his camp, and the commanding officers who use every loophole they can find to keep him in the bush.
name: Robert McNeill (Part 3)

description: Everyone’s favorite robot is back in a tale set before the hit film! And now he’s going to find out what exactly is in the mysterious spaceship that has crashed on Earth. WALL•E avoids his menacing boss BULL•E while helping a new “friend” solve a whole new mystery! A can’t-miss issue of WALL•E for kids and adults alike!
name: Out There Part 2

description: There's no business like trash business! WALL-E helps his new friend repair his spaceship but is soon captured by his trash-talking boss BULL-E. Will WALL-E escape? Will his new friend get back to where he came from? The adventure heats up in this all-new WALL-E tale.
name: Out There, Part 3

description: What starts as a desert survival exercise for the Joes turns into a fight for survival, with COBRA soldiers sent to find the Pit. Unarmed and out of communication, Covergirl, Downtown, and Tripwire must outwit, outlast, and outkill COBRA's best if they want to stay alive and prevent the disclosure of the Pit's secret location. The start of an all-new storyline, featuring art by S.L. Gallant (G.I. Joe Origins: Mainframe).

Zach is a flie clerk in a dead end job... or is he really a super-villain hiding in Witness Protection? As his powers begin to return, our anti-hero's life begins to unravel in a dark and explosive fashion. INCOGNITO is the sexy black comic pulp tale that you'll never forget!
name: TPB

description: It's the fight of the century - Atomic Robo versus Dr. Dinosaur! Time travel! Crystals! Bazookas! And the dinosaurs who use them! Yes, this comic will change your life forever. The explosive conclusion to the story that began in Red 5 Comics Free Comic Book Day 2009!
name: Why Dr. Dinosaur Hates Atomic Robo

volume.name: Atomic Robo and the Revenge of the Vampire Dimension

description:
An all-reprint issue.

  1. "The Immortal Destiny" In the opening story, we find out the origins of Dr. Fate. How the young lad, Kent Nelson loses his father at an archaeological dig and gains the power of Dr. Fate. Reprinted from DC Special Series #10.
  2. Golden Age Classic - The second story is an old classic of Doctor Fate. He thinks he's destroyed the evil scientist Wotan. He needs to confirm his death and enters the Region of the Styx. He discover Wotan is not dead and heads back to the world of men to track him down and put a stop to his evil plans. Reprinted from More Fun Comics #56.
  3. In the last story, we find Dr. Fate being drawn out by a sense of foreboding. Meanwhile at the Boston Museum of Egyptology, something is amiss with the new exhibit. From the antiquities comes the evil Khalis! Mortal enemy of Nabu. Khalis steals Dr. Fate's amulet and leaves him for dead. Dr. Fate must now get back his amulet and stop Khalis. Reprinted from 1st Issue Special #9.
name: This Immortal Destiny

With its four cannon and six machine-guns even the ordinary, standard Beaufighter packed a terrific punch. This story is about an extraordinary one. An experimental job, fitted with a huge gun in a special mounting, it could fire projectiles as big as the shells from field artillery.
name: Flying Destroyer

description:
The military policemen stood ankle-deep in the snow at a cross-roads in the Ardennes. Their uniforms, their slouch, and the constant motion of their jaws as they chewed gum marked them clearly as Americans. And that's just exactly what any who saw them were meant to think.

But those "Yanks" were in fact crack Nazi troops in disguise, all planning to bring off the biggest shock of the war...

First published in 1970.
name: And Everywhere That Casey Went....

description:
Such a nice, quiet-spoken gentlemen he was. What could he be? a dentist? A clerk, perhaps? Maybe he worked in a library or something like that.

Well, that just what you were supposed to think. The less you knew about him, the better it was for the security of your country.

For Mr Smith was a secret agent, and although he was mild of manner he was a deadly as a striking cobra.
name: The Dangerous Mr. Smith

description:
The Japs had been taken completely by surprise. Six of their ships had exploded right in the middle of Palungbang harbour, hundreds of miles inside their own territory!

What had happened? Who had done this? A bunch of British sailors and Australian soldiers, that's who.

Very tough guys, every one of them - who spent as much time scrapping with each other as they did fighting the Japs!
name: The Sea Riders

description: As Flying Office Tim Walker climbed into his Hurricane he knew that this was the final test. All the months of night-fighter training had led up to this. If he failed he could pay with his life, for he was fighting a man with a grudge against his squadron. Only Tim could end this reign of terror - and he knew it!
name: Fight In The Night

description: When a small alien baby in a space ship lands in the middle of a Midwestern cornfield, the course of mankind on Earth changes forever! Babylon 5 creator and AMAZING SPIDER-MAN writer J. Michael Straczynski presents a new vision of a world about to give birth to its first generation of super heroes! Follow the origins of these new heroes and anti-heroes - from their birth through adulthood - and examine how their lives and abilities change and shape the world around them. One of comics' best-selling mature readers series ever, SUPREME POWER is a hard-edged, mature and deeply personal saga that pushes the limits of the form into new, uncharted territory. Collecting SUPREME POWER #1-6.
name: Supreme Power: Contact

description: The heroes have arrived. You've watched them grow. You've learned their secrets. And now, you're about to see them change the world for better or for worse! When a god-like Hyperion discovers his whole life has actually been an elaborate government-made lie, his reaction could mean the end of the Earth! Do the world's other super-powered beings have any chance at stopping Hyperion if the truth sends him over the edge? Collecting SUPREME POWER #7-12.
name: Supreme Power: Powers and Principalities

description: In their first adventure as a team, Hyperion, Blur and Nighthawk - the newly formed Squadron - have a long-overdue showdown with the super-powered serial killer who's been terrorizing the nation! But will they live long enough to stop him? Plus: What does the most powerful being on the planet do when he finds out he's been manipulated, and that his whole life is practically a lie? How will Hyperion react, and what does that mean for the rest of humanity - and the government that's organized these deceitful machinations? Collecting SUPREME POWER #13-18.
name: Supreme Power: High Command
OVNEs - Objetos Voadores Nada Engraçados

description: Now that the world knows his dark secret, Hyperion suddenly finds himself both alone and hunted. Four new super-powered individuals - each based on a character from the original Squadron Supreme - are after his hide, and they've got the will and means to take him down! Collecting SUPREME POWER: HYPERION #1-5.
name: Supreme Power: Hyperion
Tio De Peixe, Peixão É
Às Voltas Com O Beijoqueiro

description: Long ago, Kyle Richmond looked into the face of madness - now, it's looking back at him. As a boy, Richmond - the man who would one day become Nighthawk - witnessed the senseless murder of his parents. There was no reason for their deaths, no provocation - they were just simply in the wrong place at the wrong time. It was a traumatic event that has left him scarred for life - and turned him into a hero more feared than the criminals he polices. Now, it's happening again...but on a much larger scale. The people of Chicago - men, women and children - are dying in the streets, victims of a monster whose thirst for slaughter cannot be quenched, whose soul is a bottomless void and whose scars run even deeper than Nighthawk's. And it's flashing a killer smile. Collecting SUPREME POWER: NIGHTHAWK #1-6.
name: Supreme Power: Nighthawk

description: A team of long-dormant Soviet super-weapons is awake, angry and heading straight at the heart of Los Angeles ready to finish World War III! The front line of defense is a team that's been together since just before nine this morning! The queen of PR starts her spin! A dead body hides more than just a murder mystery! AND AND AND - a super-sex tape! What on Earth could justify the use of that many exclamation points? Surely, it could only be The Order, written by Matt Fraction (IMMORTAL IRON FIST, PUNISHER WAR JOURNAL) with art by the amazing Barry Kitson. Collecting THE ORDER #1-7.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: The Order: The Next Right Thing

name: So Macht Man Ein Teenage Idol

description:
Reprints Fantastic Four #35 - Diablo takes control of the Dragon Man android and wreaks havoc on ESU.

Reprints Tales of Suspense #62 "Break-Out in Cell Block 10!" - Cap stops an attempted escape by the most dangerous convicts of Cell Block 10.

Reprints Tales of Suspense #69 "If I Die, Let It Be With Honor" - Boris Bullski constructs a suit of armor naming himself Titanium Man and challenges Iron Man to a fight in front of live TV.

Reprints Strange Tales #138 "If Eternity Should Fail!" - Dr. Strange finally comes face-to-face with Eternity only to learn he already has the power he needs. Strange then returns to the cave to find his master gone. Mordo's spirits lead him to Mordo, who tells Strange "The game is lost!"
name: Calamity on the Campus

description:
The Incredible Hulk

Reprints Fantastic Four #12 - After The Thing is mistakenly attacked by the Army who assumes him to be The Hulk, General Ross enlists the help of the Fantastic Four to apprehend The Hulk who he believes to be responsible for the sabotage of his missile installations.

The Mad Menace of the Macabre Mole Man

Reprints Fantastic Four #31 "The Mad Menace of the Macabre Mole Man" - A massive earthquake strikes New York and when the Fantastic Four investigates they find an entire city block missing. The Mole Man to discourage the Fantastic Four from interrupting his plans takes Sue as a hostage and forces the others to do his bidding.
name: The Fantastic Four meets The Incredible Hulk
